Download PureAuth-V2.7.jar.

Upload it to your /plugins folder.

Note: You can now remove ProtocolLib if it's not required by your other plugins.

Restart the server. PureAuth is now a standalone security solution.

2. Initial Configuration
Navigate to the /plugins/PureAuth folder and open config.yml.

Database: The default is SQLITE. For larger networks, change this to MYSQL and fill in your credentials.

Discord: To enable alerts, set enabled: true and paste your link into webhook_url.

3. Activation
After saving the file, type /pureauth reload ingame or in the console.

Done! Your server is now secured by PureAuth.
